DESCRIPTION OF NONCONFORMANCE
-------------------------------
During final visual inspection of LOT-2026-{{ run_id[:4] }}-015,
twelve (12) units were identified with cosmetic defects on the
device enclosure. Defects consist of light surface scratches
(0.5–1.2mm length) on the polycarbonate display cover, not
affecting device functionality or patient safety.

INVESTIGATION
---------------
  Root Cause Analysis:
  • Scratches traced to handling during ultrasonic welding station
  • Protective film was removed prior to welding (should remain
    until post-weld inspection)
  • Operator followed outdated work instruction WI-ASM-022 Rev B
    (current is Rev C, which specifies film retention)

  Contributing Factors:
  • Work instruction revision not communicated during shift handover
  • Old revision copies not removed from workstation

